  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Using <i>y</i> = <i>mx</i> + <i>b</i> with <i>m</i> = &minus;&frac14; and <i>b</i> = 5 gives <i>y</i> = &minus;&frac14;<i>x</i> + 5.</p><p>Choices B, C, and D are incorrect because they use the wrong sign for the slope, the <i>y</i>-intercept, or both.</p>",
